---
import GuideLayout from "../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../data/site-config";
import { buildBreadcrumbs } from "../lib/seo";

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Home", url: "https://arabiaexpat.com/" },
  { name: "Contact", url: "https://arabiaexpat.com/contact/" },
];
const schemas = [buildBreadcrumbs(breadcrumbs)];
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Contact Us: Questions About Gulf Expat Guides and Tips"
  description="Contact the Arabia Expat team for questions about visa guides, daily life resources, and Gulf expat information for the UAE, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia."
  canonical="/contact/"
  schemas={schemas}
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: "Home", url: "/" }, { name: "Contact", url: "/contact/" }]}
>
  <h1>Contact Us</h1>

  <p>Have a question about our visa guides, daily life resources, or expat guides? The Arabia Expat team welcomes your feedback. Accuracy is our top priority, and your input helps us maintain the most reliable expat resource for the Gulf region.</p>

  <h2>Email Us</h2>

  <p>The most effective way to reach us is by email:</p>

  <p><strong><a href="mailto:contact@arabiaexpat.com">contact@arabiaexpat.com</a></strong></p>

  <p>We aim to respond to all enquiries within <strong>48 working hours</strong>. Messages received over weekends or public holidays will be addressed on the next working day.</p>

  <h2>When to Contact Us</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Data corrections:</strong> if you notice outdated visa requirements, incorrect school information, or inaccurate utility costs, please let us know with the specific page URL and your source reference.</li>
    <li><strong>Regulatory updates:</strong> if a country has amended its visa rules, driving licence requirements, or utility regulations and our content does not yet reflect these changes.</li>
    <li><strong>Content suggestions:</strong> if you would like us to cover a new topic relevant to Gulf expats.</li>
    <li><strong>Salary and employment queries:</strong> for salary data, gratuity calculators, and labor law information, please visit our sister site <a href="https://taxfreesalaries.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">taxfreesalaries.com</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Arabia Expat an official government resource?</h3>
  <p>No. Arabia Expat is an independent informational website. We are not affiliated with any government ministry or employer. Our data is sourced from official government publications, recruitment platform surveys, and industry reports. For official employment matters, refer directly to <a href="https://www.mohre.gov.ae" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MoHRE</a> (UAE), <a href="https://hrsd.gov.sa" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MHRSD</a> (Saudi Arabia), or <a href="https://www.adlsa.gov.qa" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MADLSA</a> (Qatar).</p>

  <h3>Can you help me find a job or sponsor my visa?</h3>
  <p>Arabia Expat is an informational resource, not a recruitment agency or visa sponsor. We do not post job listings, process applications, or provide visa sponsorship. For job searches, we recommend platforms such as <a href="https://www.bayt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bayt.com</a>, <a href="https://www.gulftalent.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GulfTalent</a>, and LinkedIn. For visa matters, consult the relevant government immigration authority or a licensed immigration consultant.</p>

  <h3>Where can I find salary data and calculators?</h3>
  <p>Salary data, gratuity calculators, and labor law information are now available on our sister site <a href="https://taxfreesalaries.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">taxfreesalaries.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>

  <p>Arabia Expat does not provide personalised legal, financial, or immigration advice. The information and calculator results on this site are provided for general informational and educational purposes only. Laws and regulations change, and individual circumstances vary. For decisions involving employment contracts, end-of-service benefits, visa matters, or financial planning, we recommend consulting with qualified professionals (lawyers, accountants, immigration consultants) with expertise in the relevant country. Please review our <a href="/terms/">Terms of Use</a> for complete disclaimers.</p>

  <h2>About the Author</h2>

  <p>Arabia Expat is founded and maintained by <strong>Mottalib Radif, MBA INSEAD</strong>. For more details about our methodology, data sources, and editorial independence, visit our <a href="/about/">About page</a>.</p>
</GuideLayout>
